<h2>Best HVAC Systems for San Jose Climate</h2>
<p>For San Jose's Mediterranean climate, heat pumps with SEER ratings of 16 or higher offer the best value proposition. These systems efficiently handle both cooling during hot summer months and provide adequate heating during mild winters without the need for separate furnaces. Variable-speed heat pumps are particularly well-suited for the region's temperature fluctuations, automatically adjusting output to maintain consistent comfort while using 30-40% less energy than single-speed units. Since cooling demands far exceed heating needs in San Jose, prioritize systems with higher SEER ratings (18-20+) over high heating efficiency ratings. Multi-zone systems work exceptionally well in larger homes, allowing different temperature control for sun-facing rooms versus shaded areas - crucial given the significant solar heat gain typical in Santa Clara County.</p>

<h2>HVAC Rebates in San Jose</h2>
<p>San Jose residents have access to substantial HVAC rebates that can reduce installation costs by thousands of dollars. Federal tax credits offer up to \$2,000 for qualifying heat pumps and central air systems installed through 2032. California's Tech Clean program provides additional rebates of \$1,000-3,000 for high-efficiency heat pumps, with enhanced incentives for low-income households. PG&E offers rebates ranging from \$500-1,500 for ENERGY STAR certified systems, plus additional incentives for smart thermostats (\$75-125) and ductwork improvements. The Bay Area Air Quality Management District also provides up to \$9,500 in rebates for replacing gas furnaces with electric heat pumps, making the switch to all-electric systems highly attractive. Combined, these programs can offset 20-40% of total installation costs for qualifying high-efficiency systems.</p>

