<p>Selecting the right HVAC contractor in San Jose requires verifying proper licensing through the California State License Board (C-20 HVAC license required), checking Better Business Bureau ratings, and confirming liability insurance coverage. Look for contractors with extensive experience in Mediterranean climates who understand the specific challenges of Santa Clara County's temperature patterns and PG&E's rate structures. Quality contractors will perform detailed load calculations using Manual J procedures, recommend appropriate system sizing (avoiding oversizing common in the area), and provide comprehensive warranties covering both equipment (10+ years) and labor (2+ years minimum). Emergency service availability is crucial during heat waves, so choose contractors offering 24/7 support with guaranteed response times under 4 hours for system failures during extreme weather events.</p>

